{
  "stem": "25639.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And secondly, you felt that whenever you were asked a question, it was so-- the question was placed in such a way or given in such a way that it completely melted me.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, I remember, I would completely-- what's the word?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I just couldn't think of the answer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was so scared, I-- as if I was surrounded by the German Army, and the German army was not even there yet.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was in elementary school, soon after the Hungarians came in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To move on now, one morning, we had a knock on the door, and that we should be ready to leave in a half an hour.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were Hungarian gendarme and German SS, four people in all.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we should turn the keys over to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, the night before, my father hear-- my father's friend came over in the middle of the night to tell my dad that tomorrow morning, the Nazis would round up all the Jews and take them all away.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was in-- we were taken away on April 15th, so it must have been on the 14th, but I don't-- about dates, just allow me to go-- to go loosely here, please.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1944, definitely.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Shortly-- a day before.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father told my brothers to go and see so-and-so and so-and-so and so-and-so and tell them that-- what will happen in the morning, and come right back.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they did, and they weren't even allowed to be outside at night because of the curfew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They came back, and that they should also notify others.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In other words, to spread the word.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were-- there were no telephones in private homes yet at this time.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
